<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Presumably Boaz Weinstein and Dan Och called u=
p their lawyers and said =E2=80=9Cthis seems unfair, is=C2=A0Sculptor allow=
ed to do this?=E2=80=9D And presumably the lawyers did not say to them =E2=
=80=9Cwell, Section 420 of the Delaware General Corporation Law sets out th=
e factors that a board of directors is allowed to consider in rejecting a m=
erger proposal at a higher price, and it says that in the case of a client-=
consent condition the board needs to=E2=80=9D etc. There is no Section 420 =
of the Delaware General Corporation Law. The stuff that the board is allowe=
d to do is not=C2=A0<em>really=C2=A0</em>written down anywhere in clear and=
 comprehensive form.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Presumably the basic thrust of the advice that=
 Och=E2=80=99s lawyers gave him was something like: =E2=80=9CI think that a=
 Delaware Court of Chancery judge, in looking at these facts, would be offe=
nded, and would think they=E2=80=99re unfair, and might enjoin the deal.=E2=
=80=9D Or: =E2=80=9CI think that a Delaware judge would think this is fine,=
 but I=E2=80=99m not sure, so we could take=C2=A0a shot.=E2=80=9D Or even: =
=E2=80=9COf the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33=
068739.259426/aHR0cHM6Ly9jb3VydHMuZGVsYXdhcmUuZ292L2NoYW5jZXJ5L2p1ZGdlcy5hc=
3B4/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf6092adb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> seven Court of Chancery jud=
ges</a> in Delaware, three would find this offensive and four would think i=
t=E2=80=99s fine, so let=E2=80=99s see.=E2=80=9D Some of this advice would =
be based on what the lawyers know of the current judges, and some of it wou=
ld be based on reading previous Delaware opinions for clues on how Delaware=
 judges would treat this case. But the essential question here really is, =
=E2=80=9Cwill a Delaware judge find this situation fair,=E2=80=9D because l=
awsuits about breaches of fiduciary duty really are about =E2=80=9Cequity,=
=E2=80=9D about the judge=E2=80=99s somewhat subjective (though informed by=
 precedent) views of fairness. (=E2=80=9CThe Court has subject matter juris=
diction over this action because it brings equitable claims and seeks equit=
able relief,=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cl=
ick/33068739.259426/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9kb2N1bWVudHMvdXNlcnMvaXF=
qV0hCRmRmeElVL3J5bTFCWnY5Q01DNC92MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC6f499e44" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #cc=
c;"> says Och=E2=80=99s complaint</a>.) And there are seven relevant Delawa=
re judges,<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-co=
lor: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a>=C2=A0and they are knowable humans with track records, and the question=
 of what is legal in US mergers and acquisitions=C2=A0to some extent boils =
down to asking how it will strike those people. This is called =E2=80=9C<a =
href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33068739.259426/aHR0c=
HM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTYtMTEtMDkvYnJhbWJs=
ZXMtcGFydG5lcnMtYW5kLW9wdGlvbnM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTAxODIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21=
lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMDE4JnV0bV9jYW=
1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0707e17c" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">legal rea=
lism</a>.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is true to a sort of surprisingly large d=
egree in American law, and particularly mergers-and-acquisition law, which =
is very much based in equity. It is similarly true of=C2=A0<em>bankruptcy=
=C2=A0</em>law, which also involves quite a lot of equitable, is-this-fair =
questions. For instance, we talk from time to time about various sorts of <=
a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33068739.259426/aHR=
0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMDcvZGlzdH=
Jlc3NlZC1kZWJ0LWRlYWwtbWFrZXMtcGVvcGxlLW1hZD9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMDE4MjNfTU9ORVlTV=
FVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzEw=
MTgmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf92fdb37" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #cc=
c;">  distressed-debt shenanigans</a> that have the basic shape of strippin=
g some value, in a distressed company, away from some creditors to hand it =
to other creditors. =E2=80=9CIs that allowed,=E2=80=9D the losing creditors=
 will ask, and the answer will to some extent depend on the words in the=C2=
=A0contract but will also depend on whether the bankruptcy judge hearing th=
e case finds it offensive.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And, while there are lots of bankruptcy judges=
 in the US, big corporate bankruptcies tend to end up with only a few of th=
em. And for the last few years, practically speaking, the question =E2=80=
=9Cis this sort of distressed-debt shenanigan allowed=E2=80=9D could often =
be reduced to =E2=80=9Cwill Bankruptcy Judge David R. Jones of the Southern=
 District of Texas find this offensive?=E2=80=9D He hears a lot of the case=
s.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I am not a close observer of bankruptcy, but I=
 have written about Judge Jones a few times around here. <a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33068739.259426/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxv=
b21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMjkvc3ZiLXMtZGVwb3NpdG9ycy1=
3ZXJlbi10LXZlcnktbG95YWw_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTAxODIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT=
1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMDE4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnb=
j1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB86f9fcff" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" i=
temscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  One time</a>, =
it was about a fairly technical issue in the Serta Simmons Bedding LLC deal=
, whether some loans had been swapped in an =E2=80=9Copen market purchase=
=E2=80=9D; he ruled that they had, saying =E2=80=9CI sit with these matters=
 every single day=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cthis is very easy for me.=E2=80=9D=
=C2=A0That struck me as about right: The guy does a lot of bankruptcies, an=
d he knows what those words mean to the market; his sense of fairness match=
ed up with what the people doing these deals probably think.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/33068739.259426/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2Fy=
dGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDctMjcvbWF0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1wcml2YXRlLW1hcmt=
ldHMtbW92ZS1tb3JlLXNsb3dseT9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMDE4MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaX=
VtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzEwMTgmdXRtX2NhbXBha=
WduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2609fae4" itemprop=3D"StoryLink=
" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Another time=
</a>, we discussed some very odd rulings about short selling, and my view w=
as, uh, he does not sit with=C2=A0<em>these=C2=A0</em>matters every day and=
 it shows.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The point is that, for good and bad, the law o=
f US corporate bankruptcy kind of boils down to David R. Jones=E2=80=99s de=
eply informed but also somewhat idiosyncratic personal views about what=E2=
=80=99s fair and what isn=E2=80=99t.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also though he was secretly living with a bank=
ruptcy lawyer while ruling on those cases<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=
=3D"#footnote-5" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inli=
ne-block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a>=C2=A0and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3306=
8739.259426/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTA=
tMTYva2V5LWp1ZGdlLXMtcmVzaWduYXRpb24tbGVhdmVzLWhlYXZ5d2VpZ2h0LWRlYnQtYm91dH=
MtaW4tbGltYm8_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTAxODIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1d=
G1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMDE4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0=
dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4f058680" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
